text: Cameron Burrell (September 11, 1994August 9, 2021) was an American male sprinter. He was the NCAA Division I champion over 100 meters in 2018. He ran for the United States relay team at the World Junior Championships in 2012 and 2019. He was the son of Olympic gold medalist and former 100 meters world record holder Leroy Burrell, and Olympic gold medalist Michelle Finn-Burrell. Burrell was born in Houston, Texas. Burrell shot himself on August 9, 2021 at a parking garage in Houston at the age of 26. ==References== Category:1994 births Category:2021 deaths Category:African-American track and field athletes Category:American sprinters Category:Sportspeople from Houston Category:Suicides by firearm in the United States
